INSERT INTO `QuizQuestion` VALUES (1,1,'According to the summary, which definition of a start-up emphasizes its experimental nature and search for a repeatable business model?','MCQ','[\"Traditional Definition\", \"Steve Blank\'s Definition\", \"US Legal Definition\", \"Longenecker\'s Definition\"]','Steve Blank\'s Definition','Steve Blank\'s definition describes a start-up as \'An organization formed to search for a repeatable and scalable business model,\' highlighting its experimental and search-oriented nature.',0,NULL),(2,1,'True or False: The Global Entrepreneurship Monitor (GEM) findings indicate that strangers expect lower returns on investments than parents do.','True/False','null','False','The summary states that GEM findings show \'Strangers expect higher returns than parents,\' making the statement false.',1,NULL),(3,1,'Which of the following is NOT listed as a motivation for angel investors?','MCQ','[\"Job creation\", \"Technology development for social needs\", \"Guaranteed high financial returns\", \"Personal satisfaction\"]','Guaranteed high financial returns','The summary lists motivations such as job creation, technology development for social needs, and personal satisfaction. It does not mention \'guaranteed high financial returns\' as a specific motivation.',2,NULL),(4,1,'What is the primary characteristic that distinguishes equity financing from debt financing?','MCQ','[\"Equity financing requires regular interest payments.\", \"Debt financing involves giving up ownership in the business.\", \"Equity financing involves the sale of ownership in the business.\", \"Debt financing has no legal obligation to repay funds.\"]','Equity financing involves the sale of ownership in the business.','The summary clearly states: \'Equity financing involves sale of ownership in business,\' while debt financing does not require relinquishing ownership.',3,NULL),(5,1,'True or False: Seed capital is typically obtained from venture capital firms and involves formal contractual agreements with high overhead.','True/False','null','False','The summary states seed capital is \'Typically from owners, friends, family\' and is \'Often obtained in exchange for equity stake with less formal contractual overhead.\'',4,NULL),(6,1,'Which Malaysian agency is specifically mentioned as providing financial assistance and equipment for agriculture-related industries?','MCQ','[\"Majlis Amanah Rakyat (MARA)\", \"Bank Pembangunan dan Infrastruktur Malaysia Berhad (BPIMB)\", \"Malaysian Industrial Development Finance Berhad (MIDF)\", \"Bank Pertanian Malaysia (BPM)\"]','Bank Pertanian Malaysia (BPM)','The summary\'s table of Malaysian government programs lists Bank Pertanian Malaysia (BPM) as providing \'Financial assistance and equipment for agriculture-related industries.\'',5,NULL),(7,1,'According to the summary, what is a key disadvantage of public offerings as a funding source?','MCQ','[\"Lack of liquidity for owners\", \"Mandatory public disclosure of company affairs\", \"Inability to raise large amounts of capital\", \"Poor corporate image enhancement\"]','Mandatory public disclosure of company affairs','The summary lists \'Disclosure: Mandatory public disclosure of company affairs\' as a disadvantage of public offerings.',6,NULL),(8,1,'True or False: Crowdfunding is described as a method with a high funding success rate and provides entrepreneurs with ongoing counseling relationships.','True/False','null','False','The summary lists \'Low funding success rate\' and \'No ongoing counseling relationship\' as potential risks of crowdfunding, making the statement false.',7,NULL),(9,1,'Which of the following is a listed advantage of using the entrepreneur\'s own money (owner\'s money) for funding?','MCQ','[\"It eliminates all personal financial risk.\", \"It builds confidence with potential investors or lenders.\", \"It is always sufficient to fully fund the venture.\", \"It requires no involvement from family or friends.\"]','It builds confidence with potential investors or lenders.','The summary states that using personal funds has the \'Strategic advantage\' of \'building investor/lender confidence.\'',8,NULL),(10,1,'What period is associated with \'Short-term Financing\' as defined in the summary?','MCQ','[\"1-8 years\", \"5-25 years\", \"Less than or equal to 1 year\", \"1-5 years\"]','Less than or equal to 1 year','The summary explicitly defines short-term financing as having a period of \'≤1 year\' and being for working capital.',9,NULL),(11,2,'According to the definition provided by technology entrepreneur Steve Blank, what is a primary focus of a start-up?','MCQ','[\"Achieving immediate profitability through traditional methods\", \"Developing a scalable and repeatable business model\", \"Focusing exclusively on non-technology endeavors\", \"Avoiding all forms of debt and equity financing\"]','Developing a scalable and repeatable business model','Steve Blank defines a start-up as an organization transitioning from an idea to executing operations with a focus on developing a scalable and repeatable business model.',0,NULL),(12,2,'What is considered a primary advantage of debt financing for an entrepreneur?','MCQ','[\"It eliminates the need for regular interest payments\", \"It provides shared ownership and profit distribution\", \"The entrepreneur maintains full ownership of the business\", \"It removes the obligation to repay the borrowed funds\"]','The entrepreneur maintains full ownership of the business','Debt financing involves borrowing funds with an obligation to repay with interest, which allows the entrepreneur to maintain full ownership without yielding business shares.',1,NULL),(13,2,'Which source of capital involves wealthy individuals providing early-stage investment in exchange for equity?','MCQ','[\"Venture Capital Firms\", \"Commercial Banks\", \"Angel Investors\", \"Public Stock Offerings\"]','Angel Investors','Angel investors are wealthy individuals interested in early-stage companies who offer localized investments in exchange for equity.',2,NULL),(14,2,'What is the primary purpose of \'Seed Capital\' as described in the document?','MCQ','[\"To fund late-stage international expansion\", \"To pay off high-interest bank loans\", \"For foundational activities like market and product research\", \"To facilitate an Initial Public Offering (IPO)\"]','For foundational activities like market and product research','Seed capital represents high-risk, early-stage investment intended for foundational activities such as market and product research.',3,NULL),(15,2,'Unlike simple funding, Venture Capital firms typically provide which of the following?','MCQ','[\"Personal credit cards for the founder\", \"Market insights, managerial support, and strategic guidance\", \"Interest-free long-term loans\", \"Guaranteed success in the stock market\"]','Market insights, managerial support, and strategic guidance','Venture capital firms provide more than just funds; they offer market insights, managerial support, and strategic guidance to help start-ups grow.',4,NULL),(16,2,'Which of these is identified as a risk associated with crowdfunding?','MCQ','[\"Giving up 100% ownership to a single entity\", \"Business plan disclosure\", \"The requirement to pay monthly interest\", \"Lack of access to online platforms\"]','Business plan disclosure','Risks of crowdfunding include potential funding failure, tax implications, regulatory uncertainties, and the disclosure of the business plan to the public.',5,NULL),(17,2,'How did Malaysia distinguish itself in the ASEAN region regarding start-up funding?','MCQ','[\"By banning all forms of equity-based financing\", \"By being the first to pass laws encouraging equity-based crowdfunding\", \"By providing government funds to all tech start-ups\", \"By eliminating the need for a Securities Commission\"]','By being the first to pass laws encouraging equity-based crowdfunding','Malaysia pioneered crowdfunding legislation in the ASEAN region by passing laws that encouraged equity-based crowdfunding.',6,NULL),(18,2,'In the context of equity financing, what is \'Private Placement\'?','MCQ','[\"An Initial Public Offering on a stock exchange\", \"Borrowing money from family and friends\", \"Selling securities privately to raise funds\", \"Using personal savings to fund a business\"]','Selling securities privately to raise funds','Equity financing common sources include public stock offerings (IPO) and private placements, which involve selling securities privately.',7,NULL),(19,2,'Why is using the \'Owner’s Money\' (personal savings) often seen as beneficial when seeking external investment?','MCQ','[\"It guarantees the business will never fail\", \"It signifies the entrepreneur\'s commitment to the venture\", \"It is a requirement by Malaysia\'s Securities Commission\", \"It automatically qualifies the business for Venture Capital\"]','It signifies the entrepreneur\'s commitment to the venture','Entrepreneurs using personal savings or credit signifies their commitment to the business, which is important to potential investors.',8,NULL),(20,2,'During the late 1990s, many start-ups were categorized as which of the following?','MCQ','[\"Traditional manufacturing firms\", \"Agricultural cooperatives\", \"Dotcoms or online businesses\", \"Non-profit social enterprises\"]','Dotcoms or online businesses','In the late 1990s, many start-ups were known as \'dotcoms\' or online businesses capitalizing on internet commerce.',9,NULL),(21,3,'A fundamental characteristic differentiating a startup from a new traditional business, according to the summary, is its explicit pursuit of a business model that is both repeatable and scalable. Which consequence is most directly linked to this characteristic when considering external financing from sophisticated investors?','MCQ','[\"Startups are primarily focused on immediate profitability, making them attractive to debt financing from commercial banks.\", \"The scalable nature of startups often necessitates larger initial capital outlays, driving them towards equity financing from venture capitalists who seek high growth potential.\", \"Repeatability implies a stable, low-risk operational model, making personal funds the most suitable and sustainable financing option.\", \"Startups, by definition, avoid \'bootstrapping\' with personal funds due to the inherent uncertainty of their business model, making them reliant on government grants.\"]','The scalable nature of startups often necessitates larger initial capital outlays, driving them towards equity financing from venture capitalists who seek high growth potential.','The summary defines a startup as searching for a business model that is both repeatable and scalable, explicitly linking it to high growth. Scalability often requires significant investment to achieve that rapid expansion, which aligns with the large capital pools and high-growth expectations of venture capitalists offering equity financing. Option A is incorrect because startups are often not immediately profitable. Option C misunderstands the implication of repeatability in the context of growth, and Option D is incorrect as personal funds are stated as the most common starting point.',0,NULL),(22,3,'An entrepreneur secures funding for their nascent tech venture by surrendering 15% of control and future profits. This financing mechanism inherently dictates that the entrepreneur will not face fixed monthly repayment obligations, even if the startup generates no revenue in its initial high-burn phase. This scenario is a definitive illustration of equity financing.','True/False',NULL,'True','Equity financing involves selling a portion of ownership in exchange for cash. The key benefit, as outlined in the summary, is that \'there is no \'payback\' or interest\' and \'if the business fails, you don\'t owe the money back.\' The trade-off is sharing profits and giving up some control, which aligns with surrendering 15% of control and future profits.',1,NULL),(23,3,'An early-stage company that has developed a novel medical device is seeking its \'very first round\' of investment specifically for initial research, product development, and refining its business plan. This phase of funding is commonly referred to as __________.','FillInBlanks',NULL,'Seed Capital','The summary explicitly defines Seed Capital as \'The very first \'round\' of investment used for early research, product development, and building a business plan.\'',2,NULL),(24,3,'Which of the following statements most accurately reflects a core tension an entrepreneur faces when choosing between debt and equity financing for a rapidly growing tech startup?','MCQ','[\"Debt financing guarantees higher returns for the entrepreneur due to compound interest, while equity financing dilutes ownership without promising profit.\", \"Equity financing secures 100% ownership and control but demands immediate, fixed repayments, contrasting with debt financing\'s flexible payback terms.\", \"The desire to retain full control and ownership favors debt financing, but this option introduces the risk of mandatory fixed payments irrespective of profitability, potentially jeopardizing early-stage cash flow.\", \"Debt financing is always preferred by venture capitalists as it scales better with technology startups, whereas equity financing is limited to personal funds and family investments.\"]','The desire to retain full control and ownership favors debt financing, but this option introduces the risk of mandatory fixed payments irrespective of profitability, potentially jeopardizing early-stage cash flow.','The summary highlights the key pros and cons: debt financing allows founders to \'keep 100% ownership and control\' (pro), but comes with the \'con\' of \'regular monthly payments regardless of whether you are making a profit.\' Equity financing, conversely, means giving up some control and sharing profits but has no payback obligation if the business fails. This option perfectly captures the mentioned tension.',3,NULL),(25,3,'In the context of Malaysian government support for entrepreneurs, financing from MIDF is primarily directed towards which specific sector?','MCQ','[\"Agriculture-related industries\", \"SME entrepreneurs for general business loans and equipment\", \"Innovation and creative ecosystem development\", \"Manufacturing and fixed assets\"]','Manufacturing and fixed assets','The table in the \'Funding in the Malaysian Context\' section explicitly states that MIDF\'s focus area is \'Financing for manufacturing and fixed assets.\'',4,NULL),(26,3,'Malaysia was the pioneering ASEAN nation to establish legal regulations for Equity Crowdfunding, thereby creating a formalized path for digital fundraising where backers receive a fractional ownership stake in startups.','True/False',NULL,'True','The summary explicitly states: \'Malaysia was the first country in ASEAN to introduce legal regulations for Equity Crowdfunding, making it a leader in digital fundraising for start-ups.\'',5,NULL),(27,3,'A key advantage of crowdfunding, particularly reward-based models like Kickstarter, is its ability to simultaneously test market demand for a product or service while raising capital, reducing overall market validation risk for the entrepreneur.','True/False',NULL,'True','The summary lists \'Benefits\' of crowdfunding, including \'A fast way to raise money and test if the market likes your idea.\' This directly supports the idea of simultaneously testing market demand and raising capital to reduce validation risk.',6,NULL),(28,3,'Which of the following investor types would be most appropriate for a startup requiring a colossal sum of capital (e.g., tens of millions) for aggressive global expansion, coupled with a need for strategic guidance and industry connections, understanding that this would entail significant dilution of founder ownership and intensive due diligence?','MCQ','[\"Angel Investors\", \"Personal Funds (Founders, Family, Friends)\", \"Venture Capital (VC)\", \"Crowdfunding (Reward-based)\"]','Venture Capital (VC)','The summary describes Venture Capital (VC) firms as providing \'huge sums of capital and expert consulting\' but being \'very selective,\' directly aligning with the scenario\'s need for colossal capital, strategic guidance, and the implicit \'significant dilution of founder ownership\' (as a \'con\' of equity financing). Angel investors provide less money, personal funds are for early stages, and crowdfunding typically raises smaller amounts.',7,NULL),(29,3,'Name two of the \'4Fs\' typically associated with the most common starting point for startup funding.','FillInBlanks',NULL,'Founders, Family, Friends','The summary identifies \'Personal Funds (The \'4Fs\'): Founders, Family, Friends, and \'Foolhardy\' investors\' as the most common starting point. Any two of Founders, Family, or Friends would be correct.',8,NULL),(30,3,'Despite the potential for raising substantial capital and gaining market validation, a significant risk associated with crowdfunding is the mandatory public disclosure of proprietary business details and intellectual property to a wide audience, even without a guarantee of achieving the funding goal.','True/False',NULL,'True','The \'Risks\' section for Crowdfunding explicitly states: \'You have to share your business secrets publicly, and there is no guarantee you will meet your funding goal.\' This aligns perfectly with the statement.',9,NULL),(31,4,'According to the executive summary, what is the primary driver behind the growing need for secure identity verification?','MCQ','[\"The decline of physical banking services\", \"The expansion of digital services\", \"The decrease in hardware costs\", \"A global mandate by cybersecurity agencies\"]','The expansion of digital services','The summary states that as digital services expand, secure identity verification becomes more crucial.',0,NULL),(32,4,'Which of the following is cited as a reason why traditional password-based methods are considered inadequate in the report?','MCQ','[\"They are too expensive to implement\", \"They are physically difficult to remember\", \"They have proven vulnerable to threats\", \"They require specialized hardware sensors\"]','They have proven vulnerable to threats','The executive summary mentions that traditional methods like passwords have proven vulnerable.',1,NULL),(33,4,'Why is face recognition specifically highlighted as a promising biometric solution compared to others?','MCQ','[\"It is the only method that uses physiological traits\", \"It requires no physical contact or extra devices\", \"It is the fastest known biometric method\", \"It is the cheapest method to store in databases\"]','It requires no physical contact or extra devices','The summary notes face recognition is promising because it\'s secure and doesn\'t require physical contact or extra devices.',2,NULL),(34,4,'The research project specifically focuses on a system built using which deep learning architecture?','MCQ','[\"SphereFace\", \"CosFace\", \"ArcFace\", \"RetinaFace\"]','ArcFace','The summary explicitly states the research focuses on a face recognition-based security system using the ArcFace architecture.',3,NULL),(35,4,'Which deep learning framework was utilized for the implementation of the project?','MCQ','[\"TensorFlow\", \"Keras\", \"PyTorch\", \"Caffe\"]','PyTorch','The summary mentions the use of the PyTorch framework for better performance and flexibility.',4,NULL),(36,4,'In the technical pipeline of the proposed system, what is the specific role assigned to ResNet-18?','MCQ','[\"Face alignment\", \"Feature extraction\", \"Face detection\", \"Data augmentation\"]','Feature extraction','The summary states the system uses ResNet-18 for feature extraction.',5,NULL),(37,4,'Which component is integrated into the system to handle precise face detection and alignment?','MCQ','[\"ArcFace\", \"ResNet-18\", \"RetinaFace\", \"CASIA-WebFace\"]','RetinaFace','The summary mentions the integration of RetinaFace for precise face detection and alignment.',6,NULL),(38,4,'What is the primary function of the CASIA-WebFace dataset in this research project?','MCQ','[\"Performance testing\", \"Threshold selection\", \"Assisting in training\", \"Final system validation\"]','Assisting in training','The summary states that the CASIA-WebFace dataset assists in training the model.',7,NULL),(39,4,'Which dataset is utilized for testing the performance of the face recognition system?','MCQ','[\"CASIA-WebFace\", \"Labeled Faces in the Wild (LFW)\", \"ImageNet\", \"MS-Celeb-1M\"]','Labeled Faces in the Wild (LFW)','The summary specifies that the Labeled Faces in the Wild (LFW) dataset is employed for performance testing.',8,NULL),(40,4,'The abbreviation \'FAR\' in the context of performance metrics stands for:','MCQ','[\"Frequency of Access Rate\", \"False Acceptance Rate\", \"Facial Alignment Ratio\", \"Feature Analysis Range\"]','False Acceptance Rate','The summary lists FAR as False Acceptance Rate under the performance metrics section.',9,NULL),(41,4,'Which metric is used to determine the point where the False Acceptance Rate equals the False Rejection Rate?','MCQ','[\"ROC Curve\", \"Accuracy Score\", \"Equal Error Rate (EER)\", \"Precision-Recall Curve\"]','Equal Error Rate (EER)','The summary mentions EER (Equal Error Rate) as a metric providing insights into optimal performance threshold selection.',10,NULL),(42,4,'According to the comparison provided, what gives ArcFace an advantage over SphereFace and CosFace?','MCQ','[\"Lower computational requirements\", \"A unique loss function\", \"The use of ResNet-18\", \"Faster training times\"]','A unique loss function','The summary states ArcFace provides enhanced accuracy due to its unique loss function compared to SphereFace and CosFace.',11,NULL),(43,4,'What is the specific architectural mechanism used by ArcFace to improve verification accuracy?','MCQ','[\"Spatial Pyramid Pooling\", \"Angular margin\", \"Dropout layers\", \"Batch Normalization\"]','Angular margin','The methodology section explains that ArcFace is known for maximizing inter-class separability with angular margin.',12,NULL),(44,4,'The report notes that the developed system is currently at what stage of development?','MCQ','[\"Commercial-ready product\", \"Prototype-level system\", \"Theoretical framework only\", \"Legacy maintenance phase\"]','Prototype-level system','The summary states that a prototype-level verification system is developed.',13,NULL),(45,4,'What limitation was explicitly mentioned regarding the datasets used in this project?','MCQ','[\"Poor image resolution\", \"Limited dataset scale\", \"Incorrect labeling\", \"Lack of color images\"]','Limited dataset scale','The summary mentions limitations due to dataset scale and the capacity for larger and more varied training data.',14,NULL),(46,4,'Which of the following is proposed as a future direction to further validate the system\'s robustness?','MCQ','[\"Switching to a password-based system\", \"Removing the RetinaFace component\", \"Performing cross-dataset evaluations\", \"Reducing the number of training epochs\"]','Performing cross-dataset evaluations','The summary identifies performing cross-dataset evaluations as a future direction to validate the system.',15,NULL),(47,4,'Why are biometric systems like face recognition considered hard to duplicate?','MCQ','[\"They use unique physiological traits\", \"They are encrypted with 256-bit keys\", \"They change every few seconds\", \"They are stored in a decentralized blockchain\"]','They use unique physiological traits','The introduction states biometric systems use unique physiological traits that are hard to duplicate.',16,NULL),(48,4,'How does the study describe the user experience of face recognition systems compared to traditional methods?','MCQ','[\"More cumbersome but more secure\", \"Easier and more natural to use\", \"Requires significant user training\", \"Only suitable for tech-savvy individuals\"]','Easier and more natural to use','The study states that face recognition offers a contactless way to verify identity, making it easier and more natural to use.',17,NULL),(49,4,'What technology is mentioned as the driver behind the improvement of accuracy and robustness in modern face recognition?','MCQ','[\"Quantum computing\", \"Blockchain ledgers\", \"Deep learning (CNNs)\", \"Optical character recognition\"]','Deep learning (CNNs)','Modern face recognition leverages deep learning techniques, such as convolutional neural networks (CNNs).',18,NULL),(50,4,'In the context of the problem statement, what is a common consequence of traditional passwords in \'security-critical\' environments?','MCQ','[\"High electricity consumption\", \"Identity theft threats\", \"Slow internet speeds\", \"Hardware degradation\"]','Identity theft threats','The introduction notes that passwords fail in security-critical environments due to threats like identity theft.',19,NULL),(51,4,'What is the primary objective of maximizing \'inter-class separability\' in the ArcFace architecture?','MCQ','[\"To reduce the number of training images needed\", \"To ensure different faces are represented distinctly\", \"To speed up the detection phase of RetinaFace\", \"To compress the size of the final model\"]','To ensure different faces are represented distinctly','The methodology explains that angular margin ensures that different faces are represented distinctly within the algorithm.',20,NULL),(52,4,'Which framework attribute made PyTorch the choice for implementing the project\'s sophisticated architectures?','MCQ','[\"Compatibility with older hardware\", \"Flexibility and efficiency\", \"Lack of dependency requirements\", \"Automatic data collection capabilities\"]','Flexibility and efficiency','PyTorch was selected due to its flexibility and efficiency in implementing deep learning architectures.',21,NULL),(53,4,'Which of the following metrics illustrates the relationship between False Acceptance Rate and False Rejection Rate at various thresholds?','MCQ','[\"ResNet-18 Accuracy Curve\", \"RetinaFace Alignment Graph\", \"ROC Curve\", \"Loss Function Gradient\"]','ROC Curve','The analysis section mentions that the ROC Curve and EER provide insights into the system\'s threshold selection.',22,NULL),(54,4,'The \'FRR\' metric in the system evaluation specifically measures:','MCQ','[\"Face Recognition Range\", \"False Rejection Rate\", \"Frequency of Repeat Registration\", \"Full Recognition Runtime\"]','False Rejection Rate','The summary lists FRR as False Rejection Rate in the metrics section.',23,NULL),(55,4,'What is the ultimate goal mentioned for future improvements in terms of data usage?','MCQ','[\"Eliminating the use of datasets entirely\", \"Training on larger, more balanced datasets\", \"Using only black-and-white datasets\", \"Using synthetic datasets instead of real images\"]','Training on larger, more balanced datasets','Future improvements include training on larger, more balanced datasets.',24,NULL),(56,4,'RetinaFace is described as essential for ensuring high precision in identifying faces under which circumstances?','MCQ','[\"Only in perfectly lit laboratory settings\", \"Across various environments and conditions\", \"Only when the user is wearing a mask\", \"Exclusively for high-speed motion capture\"]','Across various environments and conditions','The summary states RetinaFace ensures high precision in identifying faces across various environments and conditions.',25,NULL),(57,4,'What does the study suggest about the distinctiveness of classes in ArcFace?','MCQ','[\"It is lower than that of traditional CNNs\", \"It is enhanced by the angular margin loss function\", \"It is irrelevant to verification accuracy\", \"It is achieved through manual image labeling\"]','It is enhanced by the angular margin loss function','The summary notes that ArcFace enhances system performance by increasing the distinctiveness between different classes (people) using angular margin.',26,NULL),(58,4,'The CASIA-WebFace dataset used in this project is characterized as having:','MCQ','[\"A small number of high-resolution professional portraits\", \"A wealth of facial images in diverse settings\", \"Only images of celebrities in the wild\", \"Infrared images for night verification\"]','A wealth of facial images in diverse settings','The experimentation section notes that the datasets provide a wealth of facial images in diverse settings.',27,NULL),(59,4,'What is the role of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) in this research?','MCQ','[\"They are used for generating fake identities for testing\", \"They help improve accuracy and robustness in face recognition\", \"They are used for storing the user\'s password\", \"They manage the system\'s database storage\"]','They help improve accuracy and robustness in face recognition','Modern face recognition leverages deep learning techniques such as CNNs to help improve accuracy and robustness.',28,NULL),(60,4,'Which problem does the project aim to mitigate by using advanced deep learning algorithms?','MCQ','[\"Slow internet connectivity\", \"Traditional password weaknesses and identity theft\", \"High cost of camera hardware\", \"Lack of digital storage space\"]','Traditional password weaknesses and identity theft','The project aim is to mitigate traditional problems (like password weaknesses) using state-of-the-art deep learning techniques.',29,NULL),(61,4,'According to the summary, what determines how often unauthorized access is falsely allowed?','MCQ','[\"False Rejection Rate (FRR)\", \"False Acceptance Rate (FAR)\", \"Equal Error Rate (EER)\", \"Accuracy score\"]','False Acceptance Rate (FAR)','The summary states that analyzing metrics like FAR makes it clear how often unauthorized access is falsely allowed.',30,NULL),(62,4,'The future direction of \'cross-dataset evaluations\' is intended to ensure what quality of the system?','MCQ','[\"System affordability\", \"Broad applicability and robustness\", \"Energy efficiency\", \"Hardware compatibility\"]','Broad applicability and robustness','Cross-dataset evaluations will ensure the system\'s broad applicability and robustness.',31,NULL),(63,4,'Which specific architectural component is mentioned as responsible for increasing distinctiveness between classes?','MCQ','[\"RetinaFace\", \"ResNet-18\", \"ArcFace\", \"LFW dataset\"]','ArcFace','The summary states ArcFace enhances performance by increasing the distinctiveness between different classes.',32,NULL),(64,4,'The project summary describes face recognition as a \'feasible solution\' primarily because of its:','MCQ','[\"Low resolution requirements\", \"Reliability and ease of use\", \"Portability across different smartphone brands\", \"Integration with blockchain\"]','Reliability and ease of use','The text states face recognition provides a feasible solution due to its reliability and ease of use.',33,NULL),(65,4,'What is the consequence of the observed \'limited data diversity\' mentioned in the limitations?','MCQ','[\"It requires the use of passwords instead\", \"It challenges the system\'s reliability and applicability\", \"It makes the system faster to train\", \"It eliminates the need for RetinaFace\"]','It challenges the system\'s reliability and applicability','Addressing limitations like limited data diversity could further enhance system reliability and applicability.',34,NULL),(66,4,'In the comparison between SphereFace, CosFace, and ArcFace, what is the shared goal of these models?','MCQ','[\"To reduce the number of features extracted by ResNet\", \"To enhance accuracy in face recognition\", \"To perform face detection without alignment\", \"To replace the need for PyTorch\"]','To enhance accuracy in face recognition','The summary compares ArcFace to previous models like SphereFace and CosFace, noting ArcFace provides \'enhanced accuracy\'.',35,NULL),(67,4,'What is the relationship between \'threshold selection\' and the EER metric in this report?','MCQ','[\"EER is the maximum possible threshold\", \"EER provides insights into the optimal threshold selection\", \"Threshold selection is performed manually regardless of EER\", \"EER eliminates the need for threshold selection\"]','EER provides insights into the optimal threshold selection','The summary explicitly states that the ROC Curve and EER provide insights into the system\'s threshold selection.',36,NULL),(68,4,'ResNet-18 is categorized in this report as a component for:','MCQ','[\"Face detection\", \"Feature extraction\", \"Loss calculation\", \"Database management\"]','Feature extraction','The technical components section mentions ResNet-18 is used for feature extraction.',37,NULL),(69,4,'Which of the following correctly describes the function of RetinaFace in the pipeline?','MCQ','[\"It calculates the angular margin loss\", \"It detects and aligns faces correctly\", \"It tests the final accuracy on the LFW dataset\", \"It acts as the primary training dataset\"]','It detects and aligns faces correctly','The summary states RetinaFace is essential for detecting and aligning faces correctly.',38,NULL),(70,4,'What specifically is being verified in the \'prototype-level verification system\'?','MCQ','[\"Password strength\", \"Face identity\", \"Device security\", \"Dataset balance\"]','Face identity','The project focus is on a face recognition-based security system for identity verification.',39,NULL),(71,4,'The CASIA-WebFace dataset is used for which stage of the machine learning pipeline?','MCQ','[\"Preprocessing\", \"Training\", \"Testing\", \"Deployment\"]','Training','The summary states that the CASIA-WebFace dataset assists in training.',40,NULL),(72,4,'According to the report, why are passwords failing in security-critical environments?','MCQ','[\"Because they require internet access\", \"Because of threats like identity theft\", \"Because they are too expensive for users\", \"Because they don\'t use PyTorch\"]','Because of threats like identity theft','The study background mentions passwords fail in security-critical environments due to threats like identity theft.',41,NULL),(73,4,'What is the key advantage of a \'contactless\' verification method mentioned in the text?','MCQ','[\"It prevents the spread of hardware viruses\", \"It makes the system easier and more natural to use\", \"It allows for verification without a camera\", \"It increases the storage speed of facial features\"]','It makes the system easier and more natural to use','The summary states biometric systems offer a contactless way to verify identity, making them easier and more natural to use.',42,NULL),(74,4,'Which architecture is highlighted for its \'angular margin\' loss function?','MCQ','[\"ResNet-18\", \"RetinaFace\", \"ArcFace\", \"SphereFace\"]','ArcFace','The methodology section notes the project employs ArcFace, known for its angular margin.',43,NULL),(75,4,'What is the primary role of the \'LFW\' dataset in this study?','MCQ','[\"To align faces detected by RetinaFace\", \"To serve as a training baseline\", \"To be employed for performance testing\", \"To validate the PyTorch framework installation\"]','To be employed for performance testing','The summary says the LFW dataset is employed for performance testing.',44,NULL),(76,4,'Which of these metrics is specifically linked to how often unauthorized access is denied wrongly?','MCQ','[\"FAR\", \"FRR\", \"EER\", \"ROC\"]','FRR','The analysis section mentions analyzing FAR and FRR to see how often access is falsely allowed or denied.',45,NULL),(77,4,'What does the study say about \'physiological traits\' in biometric systems?','MCQ','[\"They are easy to change and update\", \"They are hard to duplicate\", \"They are only accessible by RetinaFace\", \"They are stored as text strings in ResNet-18\"]','They are hard to duplicate','The summary states biometrics use unique physiological traits that are hard to duplicate.',46,NULL),(78,4,'Why is the PyTorch framework considered suitable for implementing sophisticated deep learning architectures?','MCQ','[\"Because it is the only framework that supports ResNet\", \"Because of its flexibility and efficiency\", \"Because it requires no knowledge of coding\", \"Because it automatically collects data from CASIA\"]','Because of its flexibility and efficiency','The methodology section explicitly attributes the selection of PyTorch to its flexibility and efficiency.',47,NULL),(79,4,'What is the main limitation related to dataset \'capacity\' mentioned in the summary?','MCQ','[\"The storage capacity of the hard drives was too low\", \"The capacity for larger and more varied training data was limited\", \"The system could only handle 18 images at a time\", \"The LFW dataset was too large for PyTorch to process\"]','The capacity for larger and more varied training data was limited','The limitations section mentions the capacity for larger and more varied training data as a challenge.',48,NULL),(80,4,'What does \'EER\' provide in terms of system optimization?','MCQ','[\"The maximum speed of the processor\", \"Insights into threshold selection for optimal performance\", \"The total number of faces in the CASIA dataset\", \"The percentage of feature extraction success\"]','Insights into threshold selection for optimal performance','The summary states EER provides insights into the system\'s threshold selection for optimal performance.',49,NULL),(81,4,'What component ensures high precision in identifying faces across various environments?','MCQ','[\"ArcFace angular margin\", \"RetinaFace integration\", \"PyTorch flexibility\", \"LFW dataset diversity\"]','RetinaFace integration','RetinaFace ensures high precision across various environments and conditions by correctly detecting and aligning faces.',50,NULL),(82,4,'The research goal involves creating a more secure verification system using what type of algorithms?','MCQ','[\"Linear regression algorithms\", \"Traditional password algorithms\", \"Advanced deep learning algorithms\", \"Sorting and searching algorithms\"]','Advanced deep learning algorithms','The objective is to leverage advanced deep learning algorithms to create a more secure verification system.',51,NULL),(83,4,'Which of the following is NOT a metric mentioned for measuring the system\'s effectiveness?','MCQ','[\"FAR\", \"FRR\", \"EER\", \"GFLOPs\"]','GFLOPs','The summary mentions FAR, FRR, and EER, but does not mention GFLOPs.',52,NULL),(84,4,'According to the detailed explanation, what makes face recognition \'easier and more natural\'?','MCQ','[\"The use of high-speed GPUs\", \"The use of cameras for contactless verification\", \"The lack of training required for the model\", \"The simplicity of the ResNet-18 code\"]','The use of cameras for contactless verification','Face recognition offers a contactless way to verify identity using cameras, making them easier and more natural to use.',53,NULL),(85,4,'What is the benefit of the \'angular margin\' in ArcFace methodology?','MCQ','[\"It reduces the size of the face image\", \"It maximizes inter-class separability\", \"It speeds up the PyTorch framework\", \"It automatically labels the LFW dataset\"]','It maximizes inter-class separability','The methodology states ArcFace is known for maximizing inter-class separability with angular margin.',54,NULL),(86,4,'What future work is suggested to validate the system\'s effectiveness across various conditions?','MCQ','[\"Upgrading to ResNet-50\", \"Cross-dataset evaluations\", \"Switching to a PIN-based system\", \"Reducing the size of the prototype\"]','Cross-dataset evaluations','Cross-dataset evaluations will ensure the system\'s broad applicability and effectiveness across various conditions.',55,NULL),(87,4,'How does ArcFace compare to previous models regarding accuracy?','MCQ','[\"It has lower accuracy than CosFace\", \"It has enhanced accuracy due to its loss function\", \"It has the same accuracy as SphereFace\", \"It has not been compared to previous models\"]','It has enhanced accuracy due to its loss function','The summary states ArcFace provides enhanced accuracy due to its unique loss function compared to SphereFace and CosFace.',56,NULL),(88,4,'Which technical component handles \'feature extraction\'?','MCQ','[\"RetinaFace\", \"ArcFace\", \"ResNet-18\", \"CASIA-WebFace\"]','ResNet-18','The summary explicitly links ResNet-18 with feature extraction.',57,NULL),(89,4,'What is the primary risk associated with traditional authentication methods like PINs?','MCQ','[\"They require too much storage space\", \"They are prone to being stolen or forgotten\", \"They cannot be used with digital services\", \"They are too fast for modern computers\"]','They are prone to being stolen or forgotten','The detailed explanation section states passwords and PINs are prone to being stolen or forgotten.',58,NULL),(90,4,'In the system\'s results analysis, what does the ROC Curve help to provide?','MCQ','[\"A list of all faces detected\", \"Insights into threshold selection\", \"The total time taken for training\", \"The layout of the ResNet layers\"]','Insights into threshold selection','The experimentation section notes that the ROC Curve and EER provide insights into threshold selection.',59,NULL),(91,4,'Which dataset provides a \'wealth of facial images\' for the study?','MCQ','[\"Only LFW\", \"Only CASIA-WebFace\", \"Both CASIA-WebFace and LFW\", \"A custom dataset not named in the summary\"]','Both CASIA-WebFace and LFW','The experimentation section states both CASIA-WebFace and LFW datasets provide a wealth of facial images.',60,NULL),(92,4,'What is the primary focus of the future improvements mentioned in the conclusion?','MCQ','[\"Reducing the accuracy of the system\", \"Expanding the dataset and enhancing architectures\", \"Replacing face recognition with fingerprints\", \"Moving from PyTorch to TensorFlow\"]','Expanding the dataset and enhancing architectures','The conclusion states future improvements include expanding the dataset and enhancing training architectures.',61,NULL),(93,4,'What is a \'physiological trait\' as used in the context of this report?','MCQ','[\"A password or PIN\", \"A unique physical characteristic like a face\", \"A specific software framework\", \"A method of data encryption\"]','A unique physical characteristic like a face','Face recognition is cited as using unique physiological traits for verification.',62,NULL),(94,4,'The \'EER\' stands for:','MCQ','[\"Estimated Error Range\", \"Equal Error Rate\", \"Extended Extraction Result\", \"Efficient Entry Ratio\"]','Equal Error Rate','The performance metrics section defines EER as Equal Error Rate.',63,NULL),(95,4,'What does the integration of RetinaFace allow the system to do with faces?','MCQ','[\"Encrypt them using PyTorch\", \"Detect and align them correctly\", \"Delete them from the CASIA dataset\", \"Compare them to passwords\"]','Detect and align them correctly','The methodology says RetinaFace is essential for detecting and aligning faces correctly.',64,NULL),(96,4,'According to the document, why is identity verification more crucial now than in the past?','MCQ','[\"Because people have more faces\", \"Because digital services are expanding\", \"Because traditional passwords have become free\", \"Because hardware is becoming less secure\"]','Because digital services are expanding','The summary links the growing need for verification to the expansion of digital services.',65,NULL),(97,4,'What is the relationship between ArcFace and \'classes\'?','MCQ','[\"Each person represents a different class\", \"Classes are different types of loss functions\", \"Classes are the different datasets used\", \"Classes are the different versions of ResNet\"]','Each person represents a different class','The text explains ArcFace increases distinctiveness between different classes (people).',66,NULL),(98,4,'What was the purpose of creating a prototype-level system?','MCQ','[\"To replace all existing security systems immediately\", \"To showcase the potential for real-world applications\", \"To test the speed of ResNet-18\", \"To collect more data for CASIA-WebFace\"]','To showcase the potential for real-world applications','The summary says the prototype was developed to showcase the potential of these technologies for real-world applications.',67,NULL),(99,4,'What does the report suggest about the \'robustness\' of modern face recognition?','MCQ','[\"It is inferior to traditional passwords\", \"It is improved by using deep learning techniques like CNNs\", \"It is only possible without alignment\", \"It is currently at its maximum possible level\"]','It is improved by using deep learning techniques like CNNs','The introduction states deep learning techniques help improve accuracy and robustness.',68,NULL),(100,4,'In the comparison of loss functions, which model did ArcFace outperform in terms of accuracy?','MCQ','[\"ResNet-18\", \"RetinaFace\", \"SphereFace and CosFace\", \"PyTorch\"]','SphereFace and CosFace','The summary compares ArcFace to SphereFace and CosFace, noting ArcFace\'s enhanced accuracy.',69,NULL),(101,4,'What was a primary finding of the experimentation with FAR and FRR?','MCQ','[\"They are always zero in prototype systems\", \"They reveal how often unauthorized access is allowed or denied\", \"They are only useful for passwords\", \"They are metrics used by RetinaFace for detection\"]','They reveal how often unauthorized access is allowed or denied','Analyzing FAR and FRR makes it clear how often unauthorized access is falsely allowed (FAR) or denied (FRR).',70,NULL),(102,4,'What technical component is described as \'powerful\' in the executive summary?','MCQ','[\"The ResNet-18 CPU\", \"The ArcFace architecture\", \"The CASIA dataset storage\", \"The LFW testing protocol\"]','The ArcFace architecture','The executive summary refers to the \'powerful ArcFace architecture\'.',71,NULL),(103,4,'According to the detailed explanation, what makes biometric traits \'hard to duplicate\'?','MCQ','[\"They are stored in PyTorch\", \"They are unique physiological traits\", \"They are encrypted with RetinaFace\", \"They require expensive cameras to see\"]','They are unique physiological traits','Biometric systems stand out because they use unique physiological traits that are hard to duplicate.',72,NULL),(104,4,'What is the goal of using \'state-of-the-art techniques\' in this project?','MCQ','[\"To mitigate traditional authentication problems\", \"To eliminate the need for future research\", \"To reduce the number of features in ResNet\", \"To make face recognition more complex\"]','To mitigate traditional authentication problems','The objective section says using state-of-the-art techniques can mitigate traditional problems.',73,NULL),(105,4,'Which of these is NOT mentioned as a limitation in the current study?','MCQ','[\"Dataset scale\", \"Data diversity\", \"System scaling challenges\", \"Incompatibility with PyTorch\"]','Incompatibility with PyTorch','The summary mentions dataset scale, diversity, and system scaling as challenges, but PyTorch is described as the selected framework.',74,NULL),(106,4,'The implementation of the system aims to create a \'more robust method for identity verification\' by leveraging:','MCQ','[\"Larger passwords\", \"Advanced deep learning algorithms\", \"Manual human verification\", \"Fingerprint scanners\"]','Advanced deep learning algorithms','The text states the aim is to leverage advanced deep learning algorithms to create a more robust method.',75,NULL),(107,4,'Why is \'face detection and alignment\' specified as essential in the summary?','MCQ','[\"To reduce the time spent training on CASIA\", \"To ensure high precision in identifying faces\", \"To prevent the system from needing PyTorch\", \"To allow the use of passwords as backup\"]','To ensure high precision in identifying faces','RetinaFace is essential for detection and alignment, ensuring high precision in identifying faces.',76,NULL),(108,4,'What does \'inter-class separability\' refer to in the context of ArcFace?','MCQ','[\"Separating images from different datasets\", \"Separating features of different people\", \"Separating training and testing phases\", \"Separating detection and alignment processes\"]','Separating features of different people','The methodology says ArcFace ensures different faces (classes) are represented distinctly.',77,NULL),(109,4,'The \'Labeled Faces in the Wild\' dataset is abbreviated as:','MCQ','[\"LFITW\", \"LFW\", \"LABFAC\", \"WILD-F\"]','LFW','The summary uses the abbreviation LFW for Labeled Faces in the Wild.',78,NULL),(110,4,'What is the role of ResNet-18 in the system architecture?','MCQ','[\"It is the primary face detector\", \"It is used for feature extraction\", \"It calculates the final FAR/FRR metrics\", \"It provides the training images\"]','It is used for feature extraction','The summary states the system uses ResNet-18 for feature extraction.',79,NULL),(111,4,'How does the research characterize the future of face recognition systems?','MCQ','[\"Limited and unlikely to grow\", \"Potential for expansion into new areas\", \"Dependent solely on better passwords\", \"Moving away from deep learning\"]','Potential for expansion into new areas','The conclusion states that enhancements could push the research into new areas.',80,NULL),(112,4,'In the summary, which term is used interchangeably with \'identity verification\'?','MCQ','[\"Authentication\", \"Encryption\", \"Data mining\", \"Feature alignment\"]','Authentication','The section \'Problem with Current Authentication Methods\' discusses identity verification.',81,NULL),(113,4,'What does the report say about the representativeness of different faces in the ArcFace algorithm?','MCQ','[\"They are represented using random passwords\", \"They are represented distinctly within the algorithm\", \"They are combined into a single class to save space\", \"They are filtered out by RetinaFace\"]','They are represented distinctly within the algorithm','The methodology states ArcFace ensures different faces are represented distinctly within the algorithm.',82,NULL),(114,4,'According to the summary, what can the ROC curve help a developer select?','MCQ','[\"The best dataset\", \"The optimal threshold\", \"The number of layers in ResNet\", \"The framework to use\"]','The optimal threshold','The summary notes the ROC curve provides insights into the system\'s threshold selection.',83,NULL),(115,4,'What does the term \'margin\' specifically refer to in the methodology of ArcFace?','MCQ','[\"The border around the face image\", \"The angular margin in the loss function\", \"The profit margin of the security system\", \"The space between training and testing data\"]','The angular margin in the loss function','ArcFace is described as maximizing inter-class separability with angular margin.',84,NULL),(116,4,'What is the primary contribution of the prototype mentioned in the achievements?','MCQ','[\"It proved that passwords are better\", \"It demonstrated the viability of modern techniques in real-world applications\", \"It showed that ResNet-18 is obsolete\", \"It collected the world\'s largest dataset\"]','It demonstrated the viability of modern techniques in real-world applications','The current achievements section states the prototype demonstrates the viability of these modern techniques in real-world applications.',85,NULL),(117,4,'Which specific technical task is \'alignment\' associated with in the document?','MCQ','[\"Training datasets\", \"Face detection (RetinaFace)\", \"Performance metrics (FAR)\", \"Loss function (ArcFace)\"]','Face detection (RetinaFace)','RetinaFace is integrated for \'precise face detection and alignment\'.',86,NULL),(118,4,'The CASIA-WebFace dataset is used to:','MCQ','[\"Evaluate the final EER\", \"Assist in training the system\", \"Align the faces in LFW\", \"Extract features using ResNet\"]','Assist in training the system','The summary says the CASIA-WebFace dataset assists in training.',87,NULL),(119,4,'What is indicated by a higher \'False Acceptance Rate\'?','MCQ','[\"The system is too strict\", \"Unauthorized access is being allowed more often\", \"The system is recognizing faces too quickly\", \"The training dataset is too large\"]','Unauthorized access is being allowed more often','The summary explains FAR measures how often unauthorized access is falsely allowed.',88,NULL),(120,4,'The system was implemented using ResNet-18. What does \'18\' likely refer to in this context?','MCQ','[\"The number of users in the system\", \"The version of the PyTorch framework\", \"The architecture\'s layer depth/configuration\", \"The age of the test subjects in LFW\"]','The architecture\'s layer depth/configuration','While the summary doesn\'t explicitly define \'18\', in deep learning (ResNet-18), it refers to the layers. The context of \'ResNet-18 architecture\' implies this configuration.',89,NULL),(121,4,'What is a identified challenge for future work according to the \'Limitations\' section?','MCQ','[\"Decreasing the accuracy of RetinaFace\", \"Addressing limited data diversity\", \"Moving the system to a desktop computer\", \"Reducing the number of metrics\"]','Addressing limited data diversity','The summary mentions limited data diversity as a challenge/limitation.',90,NULL),(122,4,'Which of the following is NOT described as a benefit of face recognition in the document?','MCQ','[\"Contactless\", \"Natural to use\", \"Requires no extra devices (uses cameras)\", \"Completely immune to all cyber threats\"]','Completely immune to all cyber threats','While the document says it is secure and robust, it does not claim total immunity to all cyber threats.',91,NULL),(123,4,'What type of neural networks are specifically mentioned as helping improve face recognition?','MCQ','[\"Recurrent Neural Networks (RNN)\", \"Convolutional Neural Networks (CNN)\", \"Generative Adversarial Networks (GAN)\", \"Radial Basis Function Networks\"]','Convolutional Neural Networks (CNN)','The introduction states modern face recognition leverages deep learning techniques, such as CNNs.',92,NULL),(124,4,'What does the research suggest about \'traditional methods like passwords\'?','MCQ','[\"They are the gold standard of security\", \"They fail in security-critical environments\", \"They are harder to steal than biometric traits\", \"They are becoming more popular in digital services\"]','They fail in security-critical environments','The study background states traditional methods fail in security-critical environments.',93,NULL),(125,4,'What is the primary function of the LFW dataset in the context of this report?','MCQ','[\"Training the ArcFace model\", \"Aligning images for RetinaFace\", \"Testing the performance of the system\", \"Serving as a backup database for passwords\"]','Testing the performance of the system','The summary states LFW is employed for performance testing.',94,NULL),(126,4,'According to the future directions, what would help further validate the system?','MCQ','[\"Using smaller datasets\", \"Cross-dataset evaluations\", \"Eliminating the use of metrics\", \"Using only one type of face\"]','Cross-dataset evaluations','The summary mentions performing cross-dataset evaluations to further validate the system.',95,NULL),(127,4,'The \'flexibility\' mentioned in the methodology refers to which tool?','MCQ','[\"ArcFace\", \"RetinaFace\", \"PyTorch\", \"ResNet-18\"]','PyTorch','PyTorch is selected due to its flexibility and efficiency.',96,NULL),(128,4,'What results from analyzing FAR and FRR?','MCQ','[\"The system\'s training speed increases\", \"Insight into how often access is falsely allowed or denied\", \"The CASIA dataset is updated\", \"The ResNet-18 architecture is modified\"]','Insight into how often access is falsely allowed or denied','Analyzing FAR and FRR makes it clear how often access is falsely allowed or denied.',97,NULL),(129,4,'Which loss function was cited as unique and responsible for ArcFace\'s performance?','MCQ','[\"Linear Margin Loss\", \"Angular Margin Loss\", \"Binary Cross Entropy\", \"Mean Squared Error\"]','Angular Margin Loss','The methodology states ArcFace is known for angular margin, which is its unique loss function.',98,NULL),(130,4,'What is the main goal of the project as stated in the introduction?','MCQ','[\"To compare ResNet-18 with other frameworks\", \"To create a more secure, accurate face verification system\", \"To collect images for the CASIA-WebFace dataset\", \"To replace cameras with PIN pads\"]','To create a more secure, accurate face verification system','The objective is to leverage deep learning to create a more secure, accurate face verification system.',99,NULL),(131,5,'What is another term used to describe white-box testing based on its methodology?','MCQ','[\"Behavioral testing\", \"Structure-based testing\", \"Functional testing\", \"Requirement-based testing\"]','Structure-based testing','White-box testing is also known as structure-based testing because it involves evaluating a system based on its internal structures or workings.',0,NULL),(132,5,'Which coverage metric ensures that all executable paths in the code have been executed at least once?','MCQ','[\"Decision Coverage\", \"Statement Coverage\", \"Data Flow Coverage\", \"Path Coverage\"]','Statement Coverage','Statement Coverage is calculated as the ratio of executed statements to the total statements, ensuring every executable path is run at least once.',1,NULL),(133,5,'Why is Statement Coverage often considered a \'weak\' metric in white-box testing?','MCQ','[\"It is too difficult to calculate for small programs.\", \"It requires expensive automated tools to implement.\", \"It might miss pathways connected to decision points that are not exercised.\", \"It focuses solely on variable definitions rather than logic.\"]','It might miss pathways connected to decision points that are not exercised.','Statement coverage is considered weak because it may fail to exercise specific branches or decision outcomes, even if every line of code is touched.',2,NULL),(134,5,'Which metric extends beyond statement execution to ensure that every possible outcome from a decision point is tested?','MCQ','[\"Boundary Coverage\", \"Decision Coverage\", \"Condition-Based Testing\", \"Exploratory Testing\"]','Decision Coverage','Decision Coverage (or Branch Coverage) ensures that each possible path emanating from a decision node in the program flow has been taken.',3,NULL),(135,5,'What is the primary focus of Data Flow Testing?','MCQ','[\"The sequence of executable statements in a graph.\", \"The informal guessing of likely error scenarios.\", \"The definition and usage of program variables.\", \"The execution of every possible path in a function.\"]','The definition and usage of program variables.','Data Flow Testing inspects program variables by examining their definitions (defs) and usage (uses) to confirm they behave as expected.',4,NULL),(136,5,'Which white-box technique utilizes a graph to identify the sequence of executed statements?','MCQ','[\"Path Coverage Testing\", \"Control Flow Testing\", \"Static Analysis\", \"Error Guessing\"]','Control Flow Testing','Control Flow Testing derives test cases from a control flow graph, which helps identify the sequence of executed statements.',5,NULL),(137,5,'What makes Path Coverage difficult to deploy in complex software systems?','MCQ','[\"It requires black-box testers to implement it.\", \"It ignores the logic branches of the program.\", \"The number of potential test cases grows exponentially with code complexity.\", \"It can only be used on dead code.\"]','The number of potential test cases grows exponentially with code complexity.','While theoretically superior, path coverage is often avoided in complex systems because the sheer number of possible execution paths makes it infeasible.',6,NULL),(138,5,'Experience-based techniques like \'error guessing\' are primarily guided by which of the following?','MCQ','[\"Internal code structure analysis\", \"Tester intuition and likely fault scenarios\", \"Control flow graph metrics\", \"The ratio of executed statements to total statements\"]','Tester intuition and likely fault scenarios','Experience-based techniques leverage the tester\'s experience and intuition to identify likely faults rather than relying on code structure.',7,NULL),(139,5,'In the context of white-box testing, why is the presence of \'dead code\' a challenge?','MCQ','[\"It makes the program run faster than expected.\", \"It provides too much data for coverage metrics.\", \"It can make statement coverage metrics misleading.\", \"It automatically converts white-box tests into black-box tests.\"]','It can make statement coverage metrics misleading.','Dead code is unreachable, so if a large portion of the code is \'dead,\' statement coverage metrics might not accurately reflect the quality of the testing.',8,NULL),(140,5,'Which technique is specifically noted as being useful for testing complex logical or nested conditions?','MCQ','[\"Condition-Based Testing\", \"Decision Coverage\", \"Statement Coverage\", \"Static Analysis\"]','Condition-Based Testing','Condition-Based Testing ensures that all conditions within decision or fork points are executed, which is particularly useful for complex or nested logic.',9,NULL),(141,6,'What is the primary purpose of Software Assurance Maturity Models according to the text?','MCQ','[\"To provide a database of known vulnerabilities\", \"To help organizations assess and improve their security processes over time\", \"To automate the coding process for developers\", \"To replace the need for penetration testing\"]','To help organizations assess and improve their security processes over time','Maturity models are frameworks that help organizations evaluate their current practices and build on experience to enhance security measures over time.',0,NULL),(142,6,'According to Steve McConnell, why is it important to detect and correct software defects early in the development process?','MCQ','[\"It allows for more complex features to be added later\", \"It makes the software run faster on older hardware\", \"It saves time and resources while preventing security vulnerabilities\", \"It eliminates the need for any future security updates\"]','It saves time and resources while preventing security vulnerabilities','Early detection and correction reduce the overall cost and time of development and prevent vulnerabilities from being baked into the final product.',1,NULL),(143,6,'Which security practice provides a structured way to understand how an attacker might exploit a system?','MCQ','[\"Assurance Cases\", \"White Box Testing\", \"Attack Patterns\", \"Gap Assessment\"]','Attack Patterns','Attack patterns are defined as structured ways to understand exploitation methods, which helps in predicting and preventing attacks.',2,NULL),(144,6,'What is the function of an \'Assurance Case\' in software security engineering?','MCQ','[\"To document the legal ownership of the software code\", \"To argue a system\'s security based on evidence to ensure no common vulnerabilities remain\", \"To provide a list of all employees who worked on the project\", \"To simulate a brute-force attack on a network\"]','To argue a system\'s security based on evidence to ensure no common vulnerabilities remain','Assurance cases act like legal cases that use evidence to prove the security of a system.',3,NULL),(145,6,'Which type of testing focuses on examining the internal workings of an application?','MCQ','[\"Black Box Testing\", \"White Box Testing\", \"Penetration Testing\", \"Gap Assessment\"]','White Box Testing','White Box Testing is defined as a method that thoroughly examines the internal workings of the application.',4,NULL),(146,6,'The BSIMM (Building Security In Maturity Model) framework establishes security benchmarks based on data from how many organizations?','MCQ','[\"Exactly 10\", \"Over 50\", \"More than 130\", \"Exactly 1,000\"]','More than 130','BSIMM uses real-world data from 130+ organizations to establish its security benchmarks.',5,NULL),(147,6,'How many domains are included in the BSIMM framework for organizing security practices?','MCQ','[\"Two\", \"Four\", \"Six\", \"Eight\"]','Four','The summary explicitly mentions that BSIMM consists of Four Domains ranging from secure code reviews to strategic planning.',6,NULL),(148,6,'What is the specific goal of Architectural Risk Analysis?','MCQ','[\"To choose the most aesthetically pleasing user interface\", \"To evaluate the design of security features to detect weaknesses before exploitation\", \"To calculate the total electricity consumption of the server room\", \"To determine the number of developers needed for a project\"]','To evaluate the design of security features to detect weaknesses before exploitation','Architectural risk analysis involves evaluating the design of features like firewalls and IDS to find weaknesses early.',7,NULL),(149,6,'Which resource is identified as a list of known vulnerabilities?','MCQ','[\"OWASP\", \"CVE Database\", \"CERT Secure Coding Initiative\", \"SDLC\"]','CVE Database','The CVE (Common Vulnerabilities and Exposures) Database is specifically listed as a resource for known vulnerabilities.',8,NULL),(150,6,'In the context of product security and risk management, what is the role of a \'Gap Assessment\'?','MCQ','[\"To fill the gap between different programming languages\", \"To identify deficits in security practices and suggest improvements\", \"To provide a backup of the system\'s data\", \"To increase the speed of the deployment pipeline\"]','To identify deficits in security practices and suggest improvements','Gap Assessment is used to find where security practices are lacking (deficits) and provide suggestions for improvement.',9,NULL),(151,7,'What is the primary benefit of correcting software defects early in the development process according to Steve McConnell?','MCQ','[\"It ensures compliance with BSIMM\", \"It saves time and resources\", \"It eliminates the need for penetration testing\", \"It automatically fixes all security vulnerabilities\"]','It saves time and resources','Steve McConnell highlights that correcting defects early saves time and resources, as earlier detection and correction prevent costly fixes later.',0,NULL),(152,7,'Which model is described as a framework for measuring and improving software security initiatives using data from 130+ organizations?','MCQ','[\"Enterprise Software Security Framework\", \"Security Development Life Cycle (SDLC)\", \"Building Security In Maturity Model (BSIMM)\", \"Software Assurance Lifecycle Model\"]','Building Security In Maturity Model (BSIMM)','BSIMM is a framework that uses real-world data from 130+ organizations to establish security benchmarks and help organizations measure and improve their security initiatives.',1,NULL),(153,7,'What do assurance cases do in the context of software security?','MCQ','[\"They list all known vulnerabilities in a system\", \"They argue a system\'s security based on evidence\", \"They simulate attacks on software\", \"They are automated testing tools\"]','They argue a system\'s security based on evidence','Assurance cases are like legal cases that argue a system\'s security based on evidence, ensuring no common vulnerabilities remain.',2,NULL),(154,7,'Which type of testing examines the internal workings of an application?','MCQ','[\"Black Box Testing\", \"Penetration Testing\", \"White Box Testing\", \"Gap Assessment\"]','White Box Testing','White box testing thoroughly examines the internal workings of an application, unlike black box testing which focuses on external behavior.',3,NULL),(155,7,'What is the purpose of architectural risk analysis?','MCQ','[\"To ensure code is reviewed by peers\", \"To evaluate the design of security features to detect weaknesses before exploitation\", \"To perform penetration testing\", \"To classify vulnerabilities in the CVE database\"]','To evaluate the design of security features to detect weaknesses before exploitation','Architectural risk analysis involves evaluating the design of security features (e.g., firewalls, IDS) to detect weaknesses before they are exploited.',4,NULL),(156,7,'Which resource provides a list of known vulnerabilities?','MCQ','[\"CERT Secure Coding Initiative\", \"OWASP\", \"CVE Database\", \"BSIMM\"]','CVE Database','The CVE database is a list of known vulnerabilities, as mentioned in the additional resources section.',5,NULL),(157,7,'In the context of the document, what does BSIMM\'s four domains include?','MCQ','[\"Only secure code reviews and penetration testing\", \"Practices ranging from secure code reviews to strategic planning\", \"Only gap assessment and security certifications\", \"Only enterprise software security framework and SDLC\"]','Practices ranging from secure code reviews to strategic planning','The BSIMM\'s four domains include various practices from secure code reviews to strategic planning, covering a broad range of security activities.',6,NULL),(158,7,'What is the role of a Software Assurance Maturity Model?','MCQ','[\"To guide the development process with security integrated throughout\", \"To help organizations assess and improve their security processes over time\", \"To provide legal arguments for system security\", \"To simulate attacks on software\"]','To help organizations assess and improve their security processes over time','Software Assurance Maturity Models help organizations assess and improve their processes over time, building on experience to enhance security measures.',7,NULL),(159,7,'Which of the following is NOT an example of a testing type mentioned in the document?','MCQ','[\"White Box Testing\", \"Black Box Testing\", \"Gap Assessment\", \"Penetration Testing\"]','Gap Assessment','Gap assessment is part of product security and risk management, not a testing type. Testing types listed are white box, black box, and penetration testing.',8,NULL),(160,7,'What is the main purpose of secure code reviews?','MCQ','[\"To evaluate the design of security features\", \"To inspect code for vulnerabilities and ensure secure coding standards\", \"To simulate attacks on the software\", \"To classify vulnerabilities in the CVE database\"]','To inspect code for vulnerabilities and ensure secure coding standards','Secure code reviews involve regularly inspecting code for vulnerabilities and ensuring it adheres to secure coding standards.',9,NULL),(161,8,'According to the summary, what is the primary purpose of Software Assurance Maturity Models?','MCQ','[\"To provide a list of known hardware vulnerabilities\", \"To help organizations assess and improve their security processes over time\", \"To replace the need for secure code reviews\", \"To automate the entire software development lifecycle\"]','To help organizations assess and improve their security processes over time','Software Assurance Maturity Models are frameworks designed to help organizations evaluate their current practices and build on experience to enhance security measures over time.',0,NULL),(162,8,'What does Steve McConnell highlight regarding the cost of correcting software defects?','MCQ','[\"Defects are cheaper to fix after the software is released\", \"The cost of fixing defects is constant regardless of the stage\", \"Correcting defects early in the development process saves time and resources\", \"Defects should only be corrected during the penetration testing phase\"]','Correcting defects early in the development process saves time and resources','Early detection and correction of defects prevent security vulnerabilities and reduce the overall cost and time required for development.',1,NULL),(163,8,'Which security practice is described as a structured way to understand how an attacker might exploit a system?','MCQ','[\"Assurance Cases\", \"White Box Testing\", \"Attack Patterns\", \"Gap Assessment\"]','Attack Patterns','Attack patterns provide a structured method for understanding potential exploits, which helps in predicting and preventing attacks.',2,NULL),(164,8,'What is the primary function of \'Assurance Cases\' in software security?','MCQ','[\"To simulate attacks on the software to find gaps\", \"To argue a system\'s security based on evidence, similar to a legal case\", \"To provide a database of known vulnerabilities like CVE\", \"To focus on the external behavior of an application\"]','To argue a system\'s security based on evidence, similar to a legal case','Assurance cases act like legal cases that use evidence to argue that a system is secure and free from common vulnerabilities.',3,NULL),(165,8,'What does architectural risk analysis involve in the context of security features?','MCQ','[\"Writing secure code following CERT guidelines\", \"Performing black box testing on the final product\", \"Evaluating the design of security features to detect weaknesses before exploitation\", \"Comparing an organization against the BSIMM benchmark\"]','Evaluating the design of security features to detect weaknesses before exploitation','Architectural risk analysis evaluates the design of security features, such as firewalls and IDS, to find and fix weaknesses early.',4,NULL),(166,8,'Which type of testing focuses on the external behavior of the application without insight into its internal workings?','MCQ','[\"White Box Testing\", \"Secure Code Review\", \"Black Box Testing\", \"Unit Testing\"]','Black Box Testing','Black Box testing is defined as focusing on the external behavior of the application without looking into its internal code or structure.',5,NULL),(167,8,'The BSIMM (Building Security In Maturity Model) framework establishes security benchmarks based on what?','MCQ','[\"Theoretical security models\", \"Real-world data from over 130 organizations\", \"Strictly government regulations\", \"The CVE database only\"]','Real-world data from over 130 organizations','BSIMM uses real-world data from 130+ organizations to establish security benchmarks and help others compare their practices against industry standards.',6,NULL),(168,8,'How many domains are included in the BSIMM framework for measuring software security initiatives?','MCQ','[\"Two\", \"Three\", \"Four\", \"Five\"]','Four','The BSIMM framework consists of four domains that include practices ranging from secure code reviews to strategic planning.',7,NULL),(169,8,'In Product Security and Risk Management, what is the purpose of a \'Gap Assessment\'?','MCQ','[\"To identify deficits in security practices and suggest improvements\", \"To provide a list of all known vulnerabilities in the supply chain\", \"To act as a legal case for system security\", \"To conduct white box testing on third-party code\"]','To identify deficits in security practices and suggest improvements','Gap assessments are used to identify where security practices are lacking (deficits) and provide suggestions for improvement.',8,NULL),(170,8,'Which resource provides a list of known vulnerabilities for security professionals to explore?','MCQ','[\"CERT Secure Coding Initiative\", \"CVE Database\", \"BSIMM Domain Report\", \"SDLC Framework\"]','CVE Database','The CVE (Common Vulnerabilities and Exposures) database is a list of known vulnerabilities used for reference in security engineering.',9,NULL),(171,9,'What is the primary defining characteristic of a Legacy Information System (LIS) according to the lecture?','MCQ','[\"The system is more than 20 years old\", \"The system resists modification and evolution to meet new requirements\", \"The system uses only relational database management systems\", \"The system has fewer than 100,000 lines of code\"]','The system resists modification and evolution to meet new requirements','An LIS is defined by its critical role combined with its significant resistance to change and evolution, rather than just its age.',0,NULL),(172,9,'Which strategy involves encapsulating a legacy component within a new software layer without modifying its internal code?','MCQ','[\"Cold Turkey migration\", \"Database Reverse Engineering\", \"Wrapping\", \"Data Cleaning\"]','Wrapping','Wrapping is a strategy that encapsulates the legacy component to provide a modern interface while keeping the core internal code unchanged.',1,NULL),(173,9,'According to the lecture, what is a major limitation of the wrapping strategy?','MCQ','[\"It requires a complete rewrite of the legacy code\", \"It is only compatible with modern NoSQL databases\", \"It does not solve inherent problems like outdated architecture or security vulnerabilities\", \"It takes 5 to 10 years to implement\"]','It does not solve inherent problems like outdated architecture or security vulnerabilities','Wrapping provides a new interface but the \'flawed engine\' of the legacy system, including its security and architectural issues, remains the same.',2,NULL),(174,9,'Which type of wrapper allows a modern application to query a legacy database by translating modern queries into the legacy format?','MCQ','[\"Backward Wrapper (b-wrapper)\", \"Forward Wrapper (f-wrapper)\", \"System Service Wrapper\", \"Function Wrapper\"]','Forward Wrapper (f-wrapper)','Forward wrappers translate modern queries into a format the legacy database understands, enabling modern apps to access old data.',3,NULL),(175,9,'According to Harry Sneed\'s classification, which of the following represents the highest level of encapsulation granularity?','MCQ','[\"Procedure\", \"Transaction\", \"Module\", \"Process\"]','Process','The five levels from lowest to highest are: Procedure, Module, Progress, Transaction, and Process.',4,NULL),(176,9,'In the context of migration, what is the primary goal of Database Reverse Engineering (DBRE)?','MCQ','[\"To delete corrupt data from the legacy system\", \"To recover the conceptual schema that expresses the underlying semantics of the data structure\", \"To automatically generate new application code\", \"To move data from the legacy system to a cloud provider\"]','To recover the conceptual schema that expresses the underlying semantics of the data structure','DBRE is the first phase of schema conversion, necessary to understand the semantics of often poorly documented or degraded legacy structures.',5,NULL),(177,9,'During the \'Data Conversion\' step of migration, what is the purpose of \'data cleaning\' (scrubbing)?','MCQ','[\"To encrypt data for security purposes\", \"To translate COBOL code into Java\", \"To identify and fix or discard corrupt or inconsistent data\", \"To increase the speed of the Extract, Transform, Load (ETL) process\"]','To identify and fix or discard corrupt or inconsistent data','Data cleaning occurs during the transformation stage of ETL to ensure the data fits the new target database model and is free of inconsistencies.',6,NULL),(178,9,'Which migration method is described as a high-risk, one-time cutover suitable only for small, less complex systems?','MCQ','[\"Chicken Little\", \"Database First\", \"Cold Turkey\", \"Forward Wrapping\"]','Cold Turkey','The Cold Turkey method replaces the entire system at once, which carries a high risk of failure and is usually only appropriate for simple systems.',7,NULL),(179,9,'Which of the following is NOT one of the three event-driven modules found within a wrapper architecture?','MCQ','[\"Message handler\", \"Interface converter\", \"I/O emulator\", \"Data scrubber\"]','Data scrubber','The lecture specifies that a wrapper consists of a message handler, an interface converter, and an I/O emulator. Data scrubbing is a part of the migration process, not the wrapper architecture.',8,NULL),(180,9,'What is the recommended approach for program conversion during migration to simplify testing?','MCQ','[\"Adding as many new features as possible to justify the cost\", \"Leaving core functionality unchanged so outputs can be directly compared\", \"Changing the business logic entirely to match modern standards\", \"Only migrating the database and deleting the old programs\"]','Leaving core functionality unchanged so outputs can be directly compared','Keeping functionality the same allows for straightforward verification by comparing the outputs of the legacy and target systems.',9,NULL);
